static int lnet_post_send_locked ( lnet_msg_t *  msg,
int  do_send 
) [static]
Parameters:
msg The message to be sent.
do_send True if lnet_ni_send() should be called in this function. lnet_send() is going to lnet_net_unlock immediately after this, so it sets do_send FALSE and I don't do the unlock/send/lock bit.
Return values:
LNET_CREDIT_OK If msg sent or OK to send.
LNET_CREDIT_WAIT If msg blocked for credit.
-EHOSTUNREACH If the next hop of the message appears dead.
-ECANCELED If the MD of the message has been unlinked.
